---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import TrustBlock from "../components/TrustBlock.astro";
import FoundingCTA from "../components/FoundingCTA.astro";
import PricingBadge from "../components/PricingBadge.astro";

const title = "AI Readiness Audit — From $1,000 | Ascend Griffin";
const description =
  "AI readiness audit for non-technical founders. Get a clear, vendor-independent read on your AI tools, vibe-coded code, and tech risk. From $1,000 · 5-14 days.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <Nav />
  <main class="about">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="about-shell">
        <p class="hero-eyebrow">01 · AI Readiness Audit</p>

        <h1 class="hero-h1">
          Read your AI build for <em>what it really is</em>.
        </h1>

        <p class="hero-lede">
          Vibe-coded prototype, vendor proposal on your desk, or an AI feature that quietly stopped working. Before you commit another $50K — a structured read from someone with no financial stake in the build decision.
        </p>

        <PricingBadge price="from $1,000" duration="5-14 days" />

        <div class="hero-cta">
          <a
            href="#book"
            class="btn-primary"
            data-modal="booking"
            data-subject="audit"
            data-source="ai-audit-hero"
          >
            Request audit →
          </a>
          <a href="#what-you-get" class="btn-ghost">See what you get →</a>
        </div>

        <p class="hero-hint">↓ Expand a section to read more</p>

        <figure class="hero-media">
          <img src="/img/audit.webp" alt="Readiness review checklist under a warm desk light" loading="lazy" width="1344" height="768" />
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>

    <TrustBlock />

    <section class="acc-section">
      <div class="about-shell">
        <details class="acc" name="audit" id="who">
          <summary class="acc-summary">
            <span class="acc-num">02</span>
            <span class="acc-label">Who this is for</span>
            <span class="acc-toggle" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="acc-body">
            <h3 class="acc-h">Two situations I read for.</h3>

            <article class="icp-card">
              <header class="icp-header">
                <span class="icp-letter">A</span>
                <h4 class="icp-title">The vibe coder who shipped something real.</h4>
              </header>
              <p>You built a working prototype in Cursor, v0, Lovable, or Claude. Twenty paying users. A few features in flight. And a growing sense that something in the foundation isn't right — but you can't read the codebase to confirm it. You don't need a developer right now. You need someone who can tell you: <em>what holds, what doesn't, and what the path to production-readiness actually looks like.</em></p>
            </article>

            <article class="icp-card">
              <header class="icp-header">
                <span class="icp-letter">B</span>
                <h4 class="icp-title">The non-technical commissioner staring at three proposals.</h4>
              </header>
              <p>Three vendor quotes on your desk. $45K to $120K for what sounds like the same project. One vendor confident, two vague, all three professionally persuasive. Without a technical background it's nearly impossible to tell which quote is honest, which is padded, and which will grow by 40% the moment a change request lands. <em>The job here is to read those proposals the way the vendor wrote them</em> — and translate that into a clear recommendation.</p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="acc" name="audit" id="what-you-get">
          <summary class="acc-summary">
            <span class="acc-num">03</span>
            <span class="acc-label">What you receive</span>
            <span class="acc-toggle" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="acc-body">
            <h3 class="acc-h">Five concrete artifacts.</h3>
            <p class="acc-lede">Not a slide deck. Not a "framework." Five things your team can act on the morning after our final call.</p>

            <ol class="modes">
              <li class="mode">
                <span class="mode-letter">01</span>
                <div class="mode-body">
                  <h4>Plain-English read of what's been built.</h4>
                  <p>Codebase, vendor proposal, or AI feature — what holds, what doesn't, in priority order. No jargon you have to Google.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="mode">
                <span class="mode-letter">02</span>
                <div class="mode-body">
                  <h4>Specific risks with dollar-impact tags.</h4>
                  <p>"This contract clause will cost you ~$8K in month 3" — not "this is something to consider." Numbers attached where I can attach them.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="mode">
                <span class="mode-letter">03</span>
                <div class="mode-body">
                  <h4>A comparison framework if you're choosing.</h4>
                  <p>Build vs. buy. Rewrite vs. patch. Vendor A vs. vendor B. Each option scored on the criteria that actually matter to your business.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="mode">
                <span class="mode-letter">04</span>
                <div class="mode-body">
                  <h4>A one-page summary your team can act on.</h4>
                  <p>Written so it makes sense to non-technical readers — co-founders, board members, finance — without me having to be in the room.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="mode">
                <span class="mode-letter">05</span>
                <div class="mode-body">
                  <h4>A 60-minute walk-through call.</h4>
                  <p>Real questions answered in real time. Not a Slack thread that goes cold on Friday.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ol>

            <div class="outcomes">
              <p class="outcomes-h">The end value isn't the report — it's knowing exactly what to do next:</p>
              <ul class="outcomes-list">
                <li>Address the surfaced risks — with priorities and impact estimates.</li>
                <li>Prepare to scale — with a clear sense of what holds and what doesn't.</li>
                <li>Sharpen product or go-to-market strategy — based on the real state of the product.</li>
                <li>Or confirm the current solution holds and you can take it to market without extra rework.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="acc" name="audit" id="not-included">
          <summary class="acc-summary">
            <span class="acc-num">04</span>
            <span class="acc-label">Not included</span>
            <span class="acc-toggle" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="acc-body">
            <h3 class="acc-h">What this audit is <em>not</em>.</h3>
            <p class="acc-lede">Saving us both a wasted first call.</p>

            <ul class="exclude">
              <li><span class="exclude-mark">→</span><span><strong>Code refactor.</strong> I read. I don't rewrite.</span></li>
              <li><span class="exclude-mark">→</span><span><strong>Vendor introductions.</strong> Separate engagement, scoped differently.</span></li>
              <li><span class="exclude-mark">→</span><span><strong>Long-term oversight.</strong> That's Project Support — also separate.</span></li>
              <li><span class="exclude-mark">→</span><span><strong>Pitch deck or fundraising help.</strong> Separate craft. I can point you to people who do this better.</span></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="acc" name="audit" id="faq">
          <summary class="acc-summary">
            <span class="acc-num">05</span>
            <span class="acc-label">Common questions</span>
            <span class="acc-toggle" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="acc-body">
            <div class="qa">
              <h4 class="qa-q">How is this different from a code review?</h4>
              <p>A code review tells you whether code is well-written. This tells you whether the <em>project decision</em> is well-made. Different question, different answer. If you also need a code review, I can point you to specialists who do that better than I would.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="qa">
              <h4 class="qa-q">What if you find nothing wrong?</h4>
              <p>That happens — and it's a useful answer too. You walk away with documented confidence that the path you're on holds. Most founders who pay for an outside read are actually looking for exactly that: the right to commit, with someone independent on record saying it checks out.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="qa">
              <h4 class="qa-q">Do you sign an NDA?</h4>
              <p>Yes. Mutual NDA template sent within 24 hours of request. Nothing from your project enters my content, my comms, or another conversation without your written approval.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </section>

    <FoundingCTA service="audit" />
  </main>
  <Footer />

  <script>
    (function () {
      const NAME = "audit";

      function openAccordionFromHash(hash: string | null) {
        if (!hash || hash === "#" || hash === "#book") return;
        let target: HTMLElement | null = null;
        try {
          target = document.querySelector(hash);
        } catch {
          return;
        }
        if (target && target instanceof HTMLDetailsElement && target.getAttribute("name") === NAME) {
          if (!target.open) target.open = true;
        }
      }

      function init() {
        const items = document.querySelectorAll<HTMLDetailsElement>(`details[name="${NAME}"]`);
        if (!items.length) return;
        const STICKY_OFFSET = 88;

        items.forEach((det) => {
          det.addEventListener("toggle", () => {
            if (!det.open) return;
            const summary = det.querySelector("summary");
            if (!summary) return;
            requestAnimationFrame(() => {
              requestAnimationFrame(() => {
                const rect = summary.getBoundingClientRect();
                window.scrollTo({ top: window.scrollY + rect.top - STICKY_OFFSET, behavior: "smooth" });
              });
            });
          });
        });

        document.querySelectorAll<HTMLAnchorElement>('a[href^="#"]').forEach((link) => {
          const href = link.getAttribute("href");
          if (!href || href === "#" || href === "#book") return;
          link.addEventListener("click", () => {
            openAccordionFromHash(href);
          });
        });

        openAccordionFromHash(location.hash);
      }

      if (document.readyState === "loading") {
        document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", init);
      } else {
        init();
      }
    })();
  </script>

  <script
    type="application/ld+json"
    set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Service",
      name: "AI Readiness Audit",
      provider: {
        "@type": "Person",
        name: "Taras Smaliukh",
        url: "https://ascendgriffin.org/about/",
      },
      areaServed: ["Ukraine", "United Kingdom", "Germany", "United States"],
      description,
      offers: {
        "@type": "Offer",
        priceCurrency: "USD",
        price: "1000",
        priceSpecification: {
          "@type": "PriceSpecification",
          minPrice: 1000,
          priceCurrency: "USD",
        },
      },
      serviceType: "Independent technical audit for non-technical founders",
    })}
  />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about { background: radial-gradient(ellipse at top right, rgba(184, 135, 58, 0.04), transparent 50%), radial-gradient(ellipse at bottom left, rgba(184, 135, 58, 0.03), transparent 40%), var(--bg-0); min-height: 100vh; }
  .about-shell { max-width: 880px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 var(--gutter); }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .about-shell { padding: 0 var(--gutter-sm); } }

  .hero { padding: 96px 0 48px; }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .hero { padding: 56px 0 32px; } }
  .hero-eyebrow { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--accent-pressed); margin: 0 0 24px; font-weight: 600; }
  .hero-h1 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(44px, 6vw, 76px); line-height: 1.02; letter-spacing: -0.03em; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0 0 28px; font-weight: 700; max-width: 16ch; }
  .hero-h1 em { font-style: italic; color: var(--editorial); font-weight: 700; }
  .hero-lede { font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 24px; max-width: 60ch; }
  .hero-cta { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 16px; align-items: center; margin: 16px 0 24px; }
  .btn-primary { background: var(--bg-ink); color: var(--text-on-ink); padding: 16px 28px; border-radius: 2px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: 0.02em; transition: background var(--dur-fast) var(--ease); }
  .btn-primary:hover { background: #2a2724; }
  .btn-ghost { color: var(--text-1); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--accent); padding-bottom: 2px; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 500; transition: color var(--dur-fast) var(--ease); }
  .btn-ghost:hover { color: var(--accent-pressed); }
  .hero-hint { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-3); letter-spacing: 0.04em; margin: 24px 0 0; }

  .hero-media { margin: 24px 0 0; }
  .hero-media img { display: block; width: 100%; max-height: 340px; object-fit: cover; border-radius: 10px; border: 1px solid var(--border-1); box-shadow: var(--shadow-md); }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .hero-media img { max-height: 220px; } }

  .acc-section { padding: 16px 0 40px; }
  .acc { border-top: 1px solid var(--border-2); transition: background var(--dur-base) var(--ease); }
  .acc:last-of-type { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-2); }
  .acc[open] { background: var(--bg-1); border-top-color: var(--text-1); }
  .acc[open] + .acc { border-top-color: var(--text-1); }

  .acc-summary { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 56px 1fr 32px; align-items: center; gap: 16px; padding: 24px 0; cursor: pointer; list-style: none; user-select: none; }
  .acc-summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .acc-summary:hover .acc-label { color: var(--accent-pressed); }
  .acc-summary:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid var(--accent); outline-offset: 2px; border-radius: 2px; }

  .acc-num { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 13px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--accent-pressed); letter-spacing: 0.04em; line-height: 1; }
  .acc-label { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(20px, 2.4vw, 26px); color: var(--text-1); line-height: 1.2; letter-spacing: -0.01em; font-weight: 700; transition: color var(--dur-fast) var(--ease); }
  .acc[open] .acc-label { color: var(--editorial); }
  .acc-toggle { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 28px; color: var(--accent-pressed); line-height: 1; text-align: right; transition: transform var(--dur-base) var(--ease); font-weight: 300; }
  .acc[open] .acc-toggle { transform: rotate(45deg); }

  .acc-body { padding: 0 0 36px 72px; max-width: 68ch; }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .acc-body { padding: 0 0 28px 0; } }
  .acc-h { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(22px, 2.6vw, 28px); line-height: 1.2; letter-spacing: -0.015em; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0 0 20px; font-weight: 700; max-width: 24ch; }
  .acc-h em { font-style: italic; color: var(--editorial); }
  .acc-body p { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 18px; }
  .acc-body p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .acc-body p strong { color: var(--text-1); font-weight: 700; }
  .acc-body p em { font-style: italic; color: var(--text-1); }
  .acc-lede { font-size: 17px; color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 28px; }

  .icp-card { margin-bottom: 28px; padding-bottom: 22px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-1); }
  .icp-card:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; padding-bottom: 0; border-bottom: 0; }
  .icp-header { display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 14px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .icp-letter { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12px; color: var(--accent-pressed); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.04em; background: var(--accent-subtle); padding: 3px 8px; border-radius: 2px; line-height: 1.2; }
  .icp-title { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(18px, 2.2vw, 22px); line-height: 1.25; letter-spacing: -0.01em; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0; font-weight: 600; }

  .modes { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--border-2); }
  .mode { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 40px 1fr; gap: 20px; padding: 24px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-1); align-items: start; }
  .mode:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
  .mode-letter { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 18px; color: var(--accent-pressed); font-weight: 700; line-height: 1; letter-spacing: -0.01em; }
  .mode-body h4 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 18px; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0 0 8px; line-height: 1.35; font-weight: 700; }
  .mode-body p { font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text-2); margin: 0; max-width: 60ch; }

  .exclude { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
  .exclude li { display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 16px; padding: 14px 0; border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--border-1); color: var(--text-2); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.55; }
  .exclude li:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
  .exclude-mark { font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--accent-pressed); font-size: 18px; line-height: 1; flex-shrink: 0; font-weight: 700; }
  .exclude strong { color: var(--text-1); font-weight: 700; }

  .outcomes {
    margin-top: 32px;
    padding: 24px 28px;
    background: var(--bg-0);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    border-radius: 0 2px 2px 0;
  }
  .outcomes-h {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--text-1);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    line-height: 1.45;
  }
  .outcomes-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .outcomes-list li {
    position: relative;
    padding: 6px 0 6px 22px;
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--text-2);
  }
  .outcomes-list li::before {
    content: "→";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 6px;
    color: var(--accent-pressed);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .qa { margin-bottom: 28px; padding-bottom: 22px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-1); }
  .qa:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; padding-bottom: 0; border-bottom: 0; }
  .qa-q { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 18px; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0 0 10px; line-height: 1.35; font-weight: 600; }
</style>
